   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4, \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\"kernelspec\": {\"display_name\": \"Python 3\", \"language\": \"python\", \"name\": \"python3\"}, \"language_info\": {\"name\": \"python\", \"version\": \"3.11.0\"}},\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"# Toxic Comment Detection\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**NLP Project 7 of 100 · Beginner Text Classification**\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"This notebook builds a **binary classifier** that detects toxic/abusive comments in online text. We use the Jigsaw/Wiki Toxic dataset and compare TF-IDF baselines against ModernBERT. This task highlights **class imbalance** challenges critical in content moderation.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Models:** TF-IDF + MultinomialNB, LogReg, LinearSVC, SGD, RF, ModernBERT\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Metrics:** Accuracy, F1, PR-AUC, ROC-AUC, Recall (safety-critical)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Handle severely imbalanced binary classification\\n\", \"2. Use PR-AUC and recall as primary metrics for safety tasks\\n\", \"3. Compare classical and transformer approaches\\n\", \"4. Understand threshold tuning for content moderation\\n\", \"5. Discuss ethical considerations in toxicity detection\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Given a user comment, predict whether it is **toxic** (harmful, abusive, threatening) or **non-toxic**. Binary classification with ~10% toxic rate.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Social platforms need automated moderation at scale\\n\", \"- Human moderators face burnout — ML prioritizes worst content\\n\", \"- False negatives (missed toxic content) cause harm; false positives hurt user experience\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|----------|-------|\\n\", \"| Source | HuggingFace `OxAISH-AL-LLM/wiki_toxic` |\\n\", \"| Task | Binary (toxic vs non-toxic) |\\n\", \"| Imbalance | ~10% toxic |\\n\", \"| Language | English |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Based on Wikipedia talk page edits annotated for toxicity. CC0 license.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Environment Setup\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\", \"for pkg in ['pandas','numpy','matplotlib','seaborn','scikit-learn','datasets','transformers','accelerate']:\\n\", \"    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace('-','_'))\\n\", \"    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\n\", \"print('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Imports\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"import os,json,warnings,random\\n\", \"import numpy as np, pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\n\", \"from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\n\", \"from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\n\", \"from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\\n\", \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression,SGDClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC\\n\", \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.calibration import CalibratedClassifierCV\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics import (accuracy_score,f1_score,classification_report,confusion_matrix,\\n\", \"    roc_auc_score,average_precision_score,PrecisionRecallDisplay,RocCurveDisplay)\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\n\", \"sns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n\", \"%matplotlib inline\\n\", \"print('Imports loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Configuration / Constants\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"SEED=42; MAX_ROWS=30000; TFIDF_MAX=15000; LABEL_NAMES=['non-toxic','toxic']\\n\", \"MODEL_NAME='answerdotai/ModernBERT-base'; MAX_LEN=128; BS=16; EPOCHS=2; LR=2e-5\\n\", \"random.seed(SEED); np.random.seed(SEED)\\n\", \"SAVE_DIR=os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath('__file__'))\\n\", \"print(f'Seed: {SEED}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Download or Loading\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"from datasets import load_dataset\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    ds = load_dataset('OxAISH-AL-LLM/wiki_toxic', split='train')\\n\", \"    df = ds.to_pandas()\\n\", \"    text_col = 'comment_text' if 'comment_text' in df.columns else 'text' if 'text' in df.columns else df.columns[0]\\n\", \"    label_col = 'label' if 'label' in df.columns else 'is_toxic' if 'is_toxic' in df.columns else df.columns[-1]\\n\", \"    df = df.rename(columns={text_col: 'text', label_col: 'label'})\\n\", \"except Exception as e:\\n\", \"    print(f'Primary dataset failed: {e}. Trying civil_comments...')\\n\", \"    ds = load_dataset('google/civil_comments', split='train')\\n\", \"    df = ds.to_pandas()\\n\", \"    df = df.rename(columns={'text': 'text'})\\n\", \"    df['label'] = (df['toxicity'] >= 0.5).astype(int)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"if len(df) > MAX_ROWS: df = df.sample(n=MAX_ROWS, random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"df = df[['text','label']].dropna().reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"df['label'] = df['label'].astype(int)\\n\", \"print(f'Dataset: {df.shape}')\\n\", \"print(f'Toxic rate: {df[\\\"label\\\"].mean():.1%}')\\n\", \"df.head()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Data Validation Checks\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"print(f'Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}')\\n\", \"print(f'Empty: {(df[\\\"text\\\"].str.strip()==\\\"\\\").sum()}')\\n\", \"df = df[df['text'].str.strip().ne('')].reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"print(f'Final: {len(df)} rows')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"df['text_len']=df['text'].str.len(); df['word_count']=df['text'].str.split().str.len()\\n\", \"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(14,5))\\n\", \"for lbl,c in [(0,'steelblue'),(1,'tomato')]:\\n\", \"    s=df[df['label']==lbl]\\n\", \"    axes[0].hist(s['text_len'],bins=50,alpha=0.5,color=c,label=LABEL_NAMES[lbl])\\n\", \"    axes[1].hist(s['word_count'],bins=40,alpha=0.5,color=c,label=LABEL_NAMES[lbl])\\n\", \"axes[0].set_title('Text Length'); axes[0].legend()\\n\", \"axes[1].set_title('Word Count'); axes[1].legend()\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'eda_distributions.png'),dpi=100); plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Class imbalance (~10% toxic) means accuracy is misleading. We prioritize **recall** (catching toxic content) and **PR-AUC**.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"fig,ax=plt.subplots(figsize=(6,4))\\n\", \"df['label'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar',ax=ax,color=['steelblue','tomato'])\\n\", \"ax.set_xticklabels(LABEL_NAMES,rotation=0); ax.set_title('Class Distribution')\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'target_analysis.png'),dpi=100); plt.show()\\n\", \"print(f'Imbalance: {df[\\\"label\\\"].value_counts().to_dict()}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Train/Validation/Test Split Strategy\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"X=df['text'].values; y=df['label'].values\\n\", \"X_train,X_test,y_train,y_test=train_test_split(X,y,test_size=0.2,random_state=SEED,stratify=y)\\n\", \"print(f'Train: {len(X_train)}, Test: {len(X_test)}, Toxic rate test: {y_test.mean():.1%}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"TF-IDF captures toxic keywords and phrases. `class_weight='balanced'` handles imbalance.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Feature Engineering\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"tfidf=TfidfVectorizer(max_features=TFIDF_MAX,sublinear_tf=True,ngram_range=(1,2),min_df=3)\\n\", \"X_tr=tfidf.fit_transform(X_train); X_te=tfidf.transform(X_test)\\n\", \"print(f'TF-IDF: {X_tr.shape}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Baseline Model: TF-IDF + MultinomialNB\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"bl=MultinomialNB(alpha=0.1); bl.fit(X_tr,y_train)\\n\", \"yp=bl.predict(X_te); ypr=bl.predict_proba(X_te)[:,1]\\n\", \"print(f'Baseline F1: {f1_score(y_test,yp):.4f}, PR-AUC: {average_precision_score(y_test,ypr):.4f}')\\n\", \"print(classification_report(y_test,yp,target_names=LABEL_NAMES))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Traditional ML Classifier Comparison\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> LazyPredict/FLAML not used for NLP per project conventions.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"clfs={'MultinomialNB':MultinomialNB(alpha=0.1),\\n\", \"      'LogReg':LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000,random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced'),\\n\", \"      'LinearSVC':CalibratedClassifierCV(LinearSVC(max_iter=2000,random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced'),cv=3),\\n\", \"      'SGD':CalibratedClassifierCV(SGDClassifier(loss='hinge',random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced',max_iter=1000),cv=3),\\n\", \"      'RF':RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200,random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced',n_jobs=-1)}\\n\", \"results=[]; trained_models={}\\n\", \"for name,clf in clfs.items():\\n\", \"    clf.fit(X_tr,y_train); yp=clf.predict(X_te); ypr=clf.predict_proba(X_te)[:,1]\\n\", \"    r={'Model':name,'F1':f1_score(y_test,yp),'PR_AUC':average_precision_score(y_test,ypr),\\n\", \"       'ROC_AUC':roc_auc_score(y_test,ypr),'Recall':f1_score(y_test,yp,average='binary')}\\n\", \"    results.append(r); trained_models[name]=(clf,yp,ypr)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"{name:15s} | F1={r['F1']:.4f} | PR-AUC={r['PR_AUC']:.4f}\\\")\\n\", \"pd.DataFrame(results).sort_values('F1',ascending=False)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Why FLAML Is Not Used Here\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> Not applicable for NLP classification.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Transformer Approach: ModernBERT Fine-Tuning\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"tr_res=None; y_pred_t=None; y_prob_t=None\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    import torch\\n\", \"    from transformers import AutoTokenizer,AutoModelForSequenceClassification,Trainer,TrainingArguments\\n\", \"    from datasets import Dataset\\n\", \"    dev='cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu'; torch.manual_seed(SEED)\\n\", \"    td=pd.DataFrame({'text':X_train,'label':y_train})\\n\", \"    if len(td)>5000: td=td.sample(n=5000,random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"    tds=Dataset.from_pandas(td); eds=Dataset.from_pandas(pd.DataFrame({'text':X_test,'label':y_test}))\\n\", \"    tok=AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\\n\", \"    def tf(ex): return tok(ex['text'],truncation=True,padding='max_length',max_length=MAX_LEN)\\n\", \"    tds=tds.map(tf,batched=True); eds=eds.map(tf,batched=True)\\n\", \"    tds.set_format('torch',columns=['input_ids','attention_mask','label'])\\n\", \"    eds.set_format('torch',columns=['input_ids','attention_mask','label'])\\n\", \"    m=AutoModelForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME,num_labels=2).to(dev)\\n\", \"    a=TrainingArguments(output_dir='./out',num_train_epochs=EPOCHS,per_device_train_batch_size=BS,\\n\", \"        per_device_eval_batch_size=BS*2,warmup_ratio=0.1,weight_decay=0.01,learning_rate=LR,\\n\", \"        eval_strategy='epoch',save_strategy='no',logging_steps=50,report_to='none',seed=SEED,fp16=torch.cuda.is_available())\\n\", \"    def cm(ep): p=np.argmax(ep.predictions,axis=1); pr=torch.softmax(torch.tensor(ep.predictions),dim=1)[:,1].numpy(); return {'f1':f1_score(ep.label_ids,p),'pr_auc':average_precision_score(ep.label_ids,pr)}\\n\", \"    t=Trainer(model=m,args=a,train_dataset=tds,eval_dataset=eds,compute_metrics=cm)\\n\", \"    t.train(); po=t.predict(eds)\\n\", \"    y_pred_t=np.argmax(po.predictions,axis=1); y_prob_t=torch.softmax(torch.tensor(po.predictions),dim=1)[:,1].numpy()\\n\", \"    tr_res={'Model':'ModernBERT','F1':f1_score(y_test,y_pred_t),'PR_AUC':average_precision_score(y_test,y_prob_t),\\n\", \"        'ROC_AUC':roc_auc_score(y_test,y_prob_t),'Recall':f1_score(y_test,y_pred_t,average='binary')}\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"ModernBERT F1={tr_res['F1']:.4f}\\\")\\n\", \"    del m,t; torch.cuda.empty_cache() if torch.cuda.is_available() else None\\n\", \"except Exception as e: print(f'Transformer skipped: {e}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Top 3 Model Selection\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"ar=results.copy()\\n\", \"if tr_res: ar.append(tr_res)\\n\", \"adf=pd.DataFrame(ar).sort_values('F1',ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"print(adf.to_string(index=False,float_format='{:.4f}'.format))\\n\", \"top3=adf.head(3)['Model'].tolist(); print(f'Top 3: {top3}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"t3d={}\\n\", \"for n in top3:\\n\", \"    if n in trained_models: t3d[n]={'yp':trained_models[n][1],'ypr':trained_models[n][2]}\\n\", \"    elif n=='ModernBERT' and y_pred_t is not None: t3d[n]={'yp':y_pred_t,'ypr':y_prob_t}\\n\", \"nc=len(t3d)\\n\", \"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,nc,figsize=(6*nc,5))\\n\", \"if nc==1: axes=[axes]\\n\", \"for i,(n,d) in enumerate(t3d.items()):\\n\", \"    sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(y_test,d['yp']),annot=True,fmt='d',cmap='Blues',\\n\", \"                xticklabels=LABEL_NAMES,yticklabels=LABEL_NAMES,ax=axes[i])\\n\", \"    axes[i].set_title(n)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'confusion_matrices.png'),dpi=100); plt.show()\\n\", \"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(14,6))\\n\", \"for n,d in t3d.items():\\n\", \"    RocCurveDisplay.from_predictions(y_test,d['ypr'],name=n,ax=axes[0])\\n\", \"    PrecisionRecallDisplay.from_predictions(y_test,d['ypr'],name=n,ax=axes[1])\\n\", \"axes[0].set_title('ROC'); axes[1].set_title('Precision-Recall')\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'roc_pr_curves.png'),dpi=100); plt.show()\\n\", \"for n,d in t3d.items(): print(f'\\\\n{n}'); print(classification_report(y_test,d['yp'],target_names=LABEL_NAMES))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Error Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"bp=t3d[top3[0]]['yp']\\n\", \"edf=pd.DataFrame({'text':X_test,'true':y_test,'pred':bp})\\n\", \"errs=edf[edf['true']!=edf['pred']]\\n\", \"fn=errs[(errs['true']==1)&(errs['pred']==0)]\\n\", \"fp=errs[(errs['true']==0)&(errs['pred']==1)]\\n\", \"print(f'Errors: {len(errs)}/{len(edf)} | FN (missed toxic): {len(fn)} | FP: {len(fp)}')\\n\", \"print('\\\\nMissed toxic examples:')\\n\", \"for _,r in fn.head(3).iterrows(): print(f'  {r[\\\"text\\\"][:100]}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Toxic content has distinctive vocabulary that TF-IDF captures well.\\n\", \"2. Class imbalance requires balanced class weights and PR-AUC evaluation.\\n\", \"3. False negatives are more costly than false positives in moderation.\\n\", \"4. Transformers capture subtle toxicity that TF-IDF misses.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Binary only — no severity levels. 2. English only. 3. Annotator bias. 4. Adversarial evasion.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## How to Improve\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Multi-label toxicity (threat, insult, obscene). 2. Threshold tuning for recall. 3. Adversarial training.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Real-time inference needed. Confidence thresholds for human review. Regular retraining.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Common Mistakes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Using accuracy on imbalanced data. 2. Not tuning thresholds. 3. Ignoring false negatives.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Find threshold giving >90% recall. 2. Add multi-label toxicity types.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Toxic comment detection is imbalanced binary NLP. 2. PR-AUC and recall matter most.\\n\", \"3. TF-IDF + LogReg with balanced weights is a strong baseline. 4. ModernBERT captures subtle toxicity.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"fm={'project':'Toxic Comment Detection','task':'binary_text_classification','models':{}}\\n\", \"for r in ar: fm['models'][r['Model']]={k:round(v,4) if isinstance(v,float) else v for k,v in r.items() if k!='Model'}\\n\", \"mp=os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'metrics.json')\\n\", \"with open(mp,'w') as f: json.dump(fm,f,indent=2)\\n\", \"print(f'Saved: {mp}'); print(json.dumps(fm,indent=2))\"]}\n",
    " ]\n",
    "}\n"
   ],
   "id": "6bf07ba4f7e78a4b"
  }
 ],
